To serve `llms.txt` and the schema files on Next.js, you'll need to set up a rewrite in your `vercel.json` file. Here’s how to do it:

1. **Create or open your `vercel.json` file** in the root of your Next.js project.

2. **Add the following rewrite rules** to the `vercel.json` file:

   ```json
   {
     "rewrites": [
       {
         "source": "/llms.txt",
         "destination": "https://geo.flowblinq.com/api/serve/{slug}/llms.txt"
       },
       {
         "source": "/schema.json",
         "destination": "https://geo.flowblinq.com/api/serve/{slug}/schema.json"
       }
     ]
   }
   ```

   Replace `{slug}` with your actual FlowBlinq slug.

3. **Deploy your changes** to Vercel. The rewrites will automatically take effect.

This setup will allow you to serve both `llms.txt` and the schema files directly from your Next.js application. If you have any questions or need further assistance, feel free to ask!
